<center>'''Level 189''' is the 190<sup>th</sup> level of the Backrooms.</center>

== Description ==
'''Level 189''', known as the '''Desolate Resort''', is an expansive and tranquil level resembling a bare, tropical resort. Wanderers cannot meet each other on this level due to the sheer distance between them, rather than it being due to [[Phenomenon 15]]. Similarly, two wanderers even noclipping during separate timeframes will never reach the same area. It consists of 3 main types of areas repeating within its Euclidean yet infinite expanse. These three areas are the ''Exterior'', the ''Hotel'', and the ''Shopping Expanse''. 

== The Exterior ==
{{Blurimage|file=Level 138 main.jpg|caption=An exterior region of the level, image taken from inside a vehicle.}}

'''The Exterior''' resembles a cloudy, outdoors environment in [[The Frontrooms]], with asphalt roads lined with uniformly spaced palm trees. There are markings on the asphalt, the condition deteriorating when not observed. Upon deterioration, they appear delaminated and indicate slight mechanical wear, though the level is nearly completely devoid of life. The sidewalks are lined with shrubbery and foliage, accompanied by regularly spaced streetlights along the path that have never exhibited usage. Blue signs are occasionally found above the road, pointing wanderers towards the inner resort.  

Despite its name, it is not a true “exterior” with a comprehensible outer rim, for it is an effectively infinite border. Roads wrap infinitely around the resort. However, reports still note the smell of the ocean nearby. 

Vehicles are found on the road occasionally, though, like most other mechanical items found in this level, they are mere shells of what they represent and do not work. They can, however, be entered, which can yield resources such as [[Almond Water]]. 

'''The Exterior''' exhibits a rough daylight cycle, though it is without order, and it is impossible even to estimate when it cycles. It is often at a temperature of around 30°C (86°F) during the day, mimicking a comfortable tropical resort. At night, the temperature drops to below -5°C (23°F), inviting wanderers into the deeper sections of the level. During this time, the only light is from the artificial, dim moon.

Any attempts to cut down the palm trees are impossible, for they will simply fall and soon disappear before reappearing back in their original location.

There are what seem to be brochures occasionally spotted drifting around '''The Exterior'''. Reading them grants information on the level, and due to the isolation wanderers are subjected to in '''Level 189''', it is where most information is derived from. 

This region of the level is, quite often, affected by [[Phenomenon 24]], causing debris to whip around at dangerously fast speeds. After such events, it is found that all resources found in The Exterior, including Almond Water, are restocked. Similarly, all markings on the ground are repainted.

== The Hotel ==
{{Blurimage|file=Hotel room 138.jpg|caption=Image of a hotel room captured in level 138. Note its neatness.}}
'''The Hotel''' is a main area within the inner zone of '''Level 189'''. '''The Hotel''' itself is a rectangular structure of, always, five floors. The facades are a solid gray, though the paint slowly peels when not being observed; this property is similarly exhibited with the markings on the road of '''The Exterior'''. Interestingly, '''The Hotel''' is the one area in the level where mechanical items do work. 

[[Phenomenon 24]] seems to have no effect on '''The Hotel'''. Also notable is that the windows cannot accurately depict the time of day outside. The location or environment may be correct, but two windows, even side by side, can show different times of day.

The first floor resembles a hotel lobby, exhibiting symmetry across the four quadrants. Each quadrant features identical furnishings, a reception counter, expansive glass double doors (exhibiting the same day-night indistinguishability as with the windows), and windows facing '''The Exterior'''. An elevator and a white staircase are found next to each other on a single side, though which you take does not matter. Generally, those seeking shelter during [[Phenomenon 24]] should take the stairs, as the elevator will drop one into [[Level 851]].

The second floor resembles a hotel buffet. Marble counters are spread in rows around the area with trays full of fresh food, aroma filling the room. The lights are bright and without buzz. Glass tables and plastic chairs are neatly placed. Do not touch anything.

The third, fourth, and fifth floors resemble guest room floors. Across their identical hallways, the floors are lined with blue carpet. Polished dark wood doors are uniformly ordered on either side. The rooms are all unlocked, and upon entry a wanderer will notice a counter with a microwave, a mini-fridge, and caffeine-related items. Notably, these items all work. There is also an empty closet, a wooden table with four seats around it, and two beds with towels folded neatly on them. A couch and a table are lined up with a TV facing a window. The TV is linked to the feed of a camera and shows a dark room, which is the nearest truly safe place in the level. All these furnishings and appliances are lined up without a single imperfection.  

During [[Phenomenon 24]], all in '''The Hotel''', even if previously in a mess, will be cleaned and restored to their original, neat states.

== The Shopping Expanse ==
{{Blurimage|file=Level 138 Mall.jpg|caption=An empty region of a shopping expanse.}}

One walking far enough into the inner zone of '''Level 189''' will eventually approach a structure known as The Shopping Expanse. It manifests as a vacant, sterile mall. Each main area in it can be classified into two types: either it has a store, or it is an empty expanse with nothing but the floor and pillars. The mall itself is a dull and faded white, yellow, or brown depending on the area and is tiled.

In the areas of the Shopping Expanse where there are stores, one will discover that all mechanical items do not work, including lights (thus plunging the whole area into total darkness during nighttime), and all items in stores change into something else, often useless, upon touch. For example, batteries could turn into a deformed plush toy upon touch. 

In the empty areas of the Shopping Expanse, one will obtain the only truly useful items found in the whole area. These items are the loaves of bread occasionally found lying on the floor, fresh yet somehow soggy. Otherwise, the empty expanses have not much to offer.

The Shopping Expanse houses the only truly safe zones during [[Phenomenon 24]] on the level. If one is able to find the crimson red door, completely out of place, and enter it, they will find themselves in a room of absolute darkness, with nothing but a security camera. Said camera is linked to every TV in the nearest hotel. The room may be cramped, but leaving it may risk discovery from '''The Disposer'''. The level may be big, but the entity is known to take its job quite seriously. Despite this hazard, the Shopping Expanse itself is completely shielded from the waters of [[Phenomenon 24]].

All windows in the shopping expanse exhibit the strange day-night indistinguishability as in The Hotel.
== Entities ==
There is only a single entity found across '''Level 189''', as noted in the strange brochures scattered in the air around the Exterior.

=== '''Entity 93''' ===
{{Entity Class|no=93|Agg=5|Int=3|Hab=Level 189|Dan=4}}{{Blurimage|file=The disposer.jpg|caption=Wanderer’s depiction of The Disposer. Notice the length of its arms.}}'''Entity 93''', also known as '''"The Disposer"''' is the sole entity inhabiting the level and is specific to '''Level 189''' alone, completing its job of cleaning the level across the infinitely large expanse. This is always done during [[Phenomenon 24]], when it will restock all items such as [[Object 1|Almond Water]], repaint all that has been delaminated, and reorder all that has been ruined by the wanderer.

As warned by the brochures scattered in the air around The Exterior, "Don't let it see you, for it won't forgive you for your mess." Despite this, it is unknown what exactly will be done to one seen by '''The Disposer''', primarily due to the isolation in this level.

There has only been one known sighting of '''The Disposer''', and the only known depiction of it is as shown to the right. The wanderer who has produced the given depiction notes its “trail of [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]]”, “unfathomable speed," and its “unrecognizable countenance." 

The only safe place for one to hide from '''The Disposer''' are the pitch-black rooms with crimson red doors found in the Shopping Expanses. Due to the variations in how long [[Phenomenon 24]] and a cleaning session take, '''The Disposer''' is a noteworthy hazard; one should always prepare [[Object 1|Almond Water]] and, if possible, food to sustain the wait. Leaving the room early risks discovery from The Disposer.

Though '''The Disposer''' oftentimes only manifests during [[Phenomenon 24]], it can also appear if anything in the buffet section of The Hotel is touched, as noted in the brochure.

== Phenomena ==
The main and most notable phenomenon on '''Level 189''' is [[Phenomenon 24]], taking place, at least as far as records have shown, exclusively within '''The Exterior''' section of the level. During these inundation events, the entity designated as "'''The Disposer'''" traverses the degraded vicinity and completes its task of cleaning and ordering displaced items or deteriorated architectural features into their original, perfect states.

While the isolation subjected to wanderers superficially resembles [[Phenomenon 15]], closer observation reveals that the isolation is simply due to the infinite size of the level and that two wanderers will never reach the exact same section of the level.
== Brochures ==
There are occasionally brochures for the resort drifting around in '''The Exterior''', though there is no wind in the level. Much information on the level is derived from it. The text seems to adjust the language to one interpretable to the reader. Below are its contents in English:{{Collapse|num=1|initial='''+ Open Brochure'''|final='''- Close Brochure'''|body=
